snippet: Backed by a big performance from quarterback Aaron Rodgers, Green Bay throttled Adrian Peterson and an overmatched Vikings team in an N.F.C. wild-card game.
abstract: Green Bay Packers beat Minnesota Vikings, 24-10, in NFC wild-card game; Packers quarterback Arron Rodgers delivers a stellar performance, completing 23 of 33 passes for 274 yards.
lead_paragraph: Backed by a big performance from quarterback Aaron Rodgers, Green Bay throttled Adrian Peterson and an overmatched Vikings team in an N.F.C. wild-card game.

headline.seo: Packers Cruise Past Vikings in N.F.C. Wild-Card Game
headline.main: Rodgers Shows Off His Arm as Peterson Cools His Heels
headline.print_headline: Rodgers Shows Off His Arm As Peterson Cools His Heels
